    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl>Morelli in <ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>264</citedRange> (no image)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>105110</citedRange></bibl>.
                   Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#jbwp-rgg-jmr2003"/>, p. <citedRange>150</citedRange> and fig. <citedRange>105</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.96</citedRange></bibl>.</p>    
              </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                    <ab>
                        <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-62839"><name nymRef="#Ἀνάξανδρος"><supplied reason="lost">Ἀ</supplied><unclear>ν</unclear>άξανδρος</name>
                        <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65429"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Πραξιάδας"><supplied reason="lost">Π</supplied>ραξιάδα</name></persName></persName>
                    </ab>
                      </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="2">
                        <lem><supplied reason="lost">Πρ</supplied>αξιάδα</lem>
                        <rdg resp="#SECir"><supplied reason="lost">Π</supplied><unclear>ρ</unclear>αξιάδα</rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Anaxandros fils de Praxiadas</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Anaxandros son of Praxiadas</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Anaxandros figlio di Praxiadas</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>أناكساندروس بن براكسيداس</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Like other funerary bases found re-used in the Eastern church, this one might come from the nearest Necropolis, i.e. the Eastern one.</p>
                <p>The excavations of the East Church were carried out by Goodchild between 1954 and 1956. Il is highly plausible that the stone had been formerly 
                    buried. For explanations about the successive re-uses, see <bibl><ptr target="#jbwp-rgg-jmr2003"/></bibl>.</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
